# Photo Gallery Requirements

## 1. Dynamic Course Gallery
- The **Photo Gallery** sidebar link must route to `/photo-gallery`.
- Gallery items must be built **dynamically** from the existing course catalog (`courseStacks`, `popularCoursePlaceholders`) — never hard-code a static-only grid.
- Each item displays course title, stack/track label, and a representative image.

## 2. Lightbox UX
- Clicking a gallery thumbnail opens a **Lightbox** modal overlay (focused image, dimmed backdrop).
- Lightbox must support **Close**, **Previous**, and **Next** controls plus keyboard (`Escape`, arrow keys).
- Trap focus inside the modal while open; restore scroll when closed.

## 3. Layout & Accessibility
- Responsive Bootstrap grid (`row` / `col-*`) inside an `eduhive-card`.
- Images use meaningful `alt` text derived from course labels.
- Match Super Travel tokens (`--eh-*`, `st-label`, `eduhive-card`) and dark-mode overrides.

## 4. Module Structure
- Keep UI under `client/src/modules/photo-gallery/`.
- Separate: `utils/buildGalleryItems.js`, `hooks/usePhotoGallery.js`, `components/PhotoGalleryGrid.js`, `components/LightboxModal.js`, `PhotoGalleryPage.js`.
